abstract: Conditions for buoyant economic growth in Brazil have rarely, if ever, been better, making 2020 a "make-or-break" year for Latin America's largest and long underachieving economy.
snippet: Conditions for buoyant economic growth in Brazil have rarely, if ever, been better, making 2020 a "make-or-break" year for Latin America's largest and long underachieving economy.
lead_paragraph: BRASILIA — Conditions for buoyant economic growth in Brazil have rarely, if ever, been better, making 2020 a "make-or-break" year for Latin America's largest and long underachieving economy.
headline_main: Brazil Economic Stars Align, Turning 2020 Into 'Make or Break' Year
headline_print_headline: Brazil Economic Stars Align, Turning 2020 Into 'Make or Break' Year

abstract: Democrats propelled President Donald Trump’s impeachment toward a historic vote by the full U.S. House as the Judiciary Committee on Friday approved charges of abuse of power and obstruction of Congress. It's the latest major step in the constitutional and political storm that has divided Congress and the nation.
snippet: Democrats propelled President Donald Trump’s impeachment toward a historic vote by the full U.S. House as the Judiciary Committee on Friday approved charges of abuse of power and obstruction of Congress. It's the latest major step in the constitut...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats propelled President Donald Trump’s impeachment toward a historic vote by the full U.S. House as the Judiciary Committee on Friday approved charges of abuse of power and obstruction of Congress. It's the latest major step in the constitutional and political storm that has divided Congress and the nation.
headline_main: Impeachment Charges Head to House; Trump Cries Anew: 'Hoax'
headline_print_headline: Impeachment Charges Head to House; Trump Cries Anew: 'Hoax'

abstract: Democratic White House hopefuls agree President Donald Trump must be defeated next year. But the unity ends there.
snippet: Democratic White House hopefuls agree President Donald Trump must be defeated next year. But the unity ends there.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democratic White House hopefuls agree President Donald Trump must be defeated next year. But the unity ends there.
headline_main: Democratic Candidates Unite Against Trump but Little Else

abstract: Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe on Friday postponed traveling for a summit with India's leader in the violence-wracked northeast, where two people have been killed in ongoing protests over a new law that grants citizenship based on religion and excludes Muslims.

lead_paragraph: GAUHATI, India — Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe on Friday postponed traveling for a summit with India's leader in the violence-wracked northeast, where two people have been killed in ongoing protests over a new law that grants citizenship based on religion and excludes Muslims.
